node.text:
This week, 15 years ago, I took Olympic ice for the first time and lived my dreams in front of billions of people around the world. While I’m not someone who lives in the memory of who they used to be, moments like these are what have made me who I am and my eyes still well up with tears of pride and thanks when I think of all the adventures that have brought me here, against all odds. 🤍
#figureskating #olympics #dreambig

node.text: 23.6.2021 Happy Olympic Day! The Olympic Games changed my life in every conceivable way. My quest to make my dreams come true taught me about hard work, determination, overcoming adversity, the thrill of accomplishment and most importantly, how to believe in myself. While the greatest moments of my life happened in front of the world, my journey was a personal one that has enriched my life and taught me so much about what we can achieve if we dream hard enough. On Olympic Day, I encourage you to follow your dreams and to help your family and friends find their voice through sport. @olympics 🤍 #olympicday #figureskating #olympian
